<%= turbo_stream_from "messages_for_conversation_#{@conversation.id}" %>
<h1 class="conversation-title">
  Try asking the following:
</h1>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center space-y-3 text-gray-500 font-mono text-sm">
  <li>Can you provide a summary of the key details from [Company Name]â€™s latest S-1 filing?</li>
  <li>What are the most common risk factors disclosed in recent S-1 filings?</li>
  <li>What valuation or share price range does [Company Name] indicate in its S-1 filing?</li>
  <li>How does [Company Name] plan to use the proceeds from its IPO as outlined in the S-1?</li>
</ul>
<br>
<!-- CHAT BOX -->
<div id="chat-box"
      data-conversation-id="<%= @conversation.id %>"
      class="chat-box space-y-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-y-auto"
      role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-relevant="additions">
  <% if @conversation.messages.any? %>
    <% @conversation.messages.order(:created_at).each do |msg| %>
      <%= render partial: "messages/message", locals: {msg: msg } %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>
<!-- FORM -->
<div id="new_message_form">
  <%= render partial: "messages/form", locals: { company: @company, conversation: @conversation } %>
</div>
